<h2>Procession organization protocol 2026</h2>
<p>21 March 2026</p>
<p><strong>Protocol for the penitential station</strong></p>
<p>From the office of the Brotherhood (Fiscalía), together with the section stewards (Diputados/as de Tramo), this protocol sets out the basic arrangements for Holy Thursday’s penitential station in 2026.</p>

<h3>Aims</h3>
<p>To support the proper running of the penitential station before, during and after the event, by listing the main tasks in each phase.</p>

<h3>Organization before the station</h3>
<p>Section stewards must arrive at the church in good time. The Fiscalía will give each steward the list of penitents in their section, plus paper and pens.</p>
<p>Church benches will be clearly labelled by section. Stewards are responsible for seating each section in order so every penitent knows their place when moving to the courtyard.</p>
<p>At least two people per section should help, given the short time available. No change of place is allowed without the steward’s agreement.</p>
<p>Once seated, stewards will remind penitents of basic rules. After the preliminary readings, those carrying insignia will collect them from the team in front of the insignia altar.</p>
<p>When the procession is called to form up, penitents will line up promptly in the central aisle, leave to the courtyard in section order, and collect candles at the door. If time allows, masks may be adjusted in the courtyard.</p>

<h3>Basic rules during the station</h3>
<p>Maintain silence and respect where possible. Many participants are minors; stewards should be understanding and flexible.</p>
<p>Keep a straight, aligned line without overtaking or falling back. Walk at an even pace. Spacing is normally about one metre (unless the brotherhood decides otherwise).</p>
<p>Any temporary or final exit from the procession must be reported to the section steward. External accompaniment (e.g. parents) should stay outside the ranks; it is not allowed in the official route (fenced area) except for justified reasons.</p>
<p>Do not raise the mask except for good reason. Disciplinary issues should be resolved by the steward, involving the Fiscalía if needed. Some stewards will use radio equipment.</p>
<p>Light candles only when stewards authorize it. Handle fire carefully: gloves can catch fire easily; burn ointment should be available. Stewards should check penitents’ wellbeing (mask, temporary exit, hydration, etc.).</p>
<p>At the end, thanks will be given for good conduct; participants are the brotherhood’s greatest asset, and will be invited to take part again next year.</p>

<h3>End of the procession and return</h3>
<p>The parish courtyard remains part of the station: masks stay on. As groups enter, insignia bearers will go inside to place insignia on the altar.</p>
<p>The station does not end until the palio float has entered; everyone in the procession must remain in the parish area until it is formally closed.</p>
<p>To limit access by outsiders once doors open, a team will control entry; stewards may assist. From at least Holy Tuesday, the Governing Board is advised to post signs stating that only procession members may enter the courtyard until the station ends.</p>
<p>The Fiscalía will distribute a summary of this protocol to participants in advance.</p>
